'''成功小孩'''（{{lang-en|Success Kid}}），或稱'''握拳寶寶'''、'''打氣小童'''，是一張照片，照片中有一個嬰兒，表情堅定地握著一把沙<ref name="abc news kidney transplant campaign">{{cite web | url = https://abcnews.go.com/Health/internet-success-kids-dad-kidney-transplant/story?id=30288035 | title = Success Kid's Dad Needs a Kidney Transplant | last = Lupkin | first = Sydney | work = [[ABC_News|ABC News]] | date = 2015-04-14 | accessdate = 2015-04-16 | archive-date = 2021-02-28 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210228122034/https://abcnews.go.com/Health/internet-success-kids-dad-kidney-transplant/story?id=30288035 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。這張照片攝於2007年，並在之後變成[[網路迷因|網路迷因]]。其受歡迎的程度使得[[CNN|CNN]]聲稱照片中的孩子薩米·格林納（{{lang|en|Sammy Griner}}）「可能是網路上最知名的孩子」<ref name="cnn success kid" />。除了在社群網站上廣泛流傳，這張圖片也被用於商業用途，並曾被[[白宮|白宮]]用來推行移民政策改革。2015年年中，格林納家族將這張圖片用於在眾籌平台[[GoFundMe|GoFundMe]]上籌措家族中父親的[[腎臟移植|腎臟移植]]。

== 歷程 ==
這個迷因源於2007年，當時萊尼·格林納（{{lang|en|Laney Griner}}）在[[Flickr|Flickr]]上傳了她兒子薩米試圖吃沙子的照片<ref name="abc news kidney transplant campaign"/><ref name="cnn success kid">{{cite web | url = http://www.cnn.com/2015/04/15/living/success-kid-dad-needs-help/ | title = 'Success Kid' appeals to social media to get his dad a kidney transplant | last = Payne | first = Ed | work = [[CNN|CNN]] | date = 2015-04-15 | accessdate = 2015-04-16 | archive-date = 2020-07-03 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200703175314/https://www.cnn.com/2015/04/15/living/success-kid-dad-needs-help/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>。這張迷因圖最初搭配的文字是「我討厭沙堡」，表示這個孩子剛才摧毀了另一個孩子堆的沙堡。最終，對於這張照片的詮釋轉變為強調這個男孩的表情和緊握的拳頭，並加上了祝賀用語，用以表示祝賀或祈求好運<ref name="the verge ROFLCon">{{cite web | url = https://www.theverge.com/2012/5/7/3005044/roflcon-when-memes-go-mainstream | title = At ROFLCon, watching memes go mainstream | last = June | first = Laura | work = The Verge | date = 2012-05-07 | accessdate = 2015-04-16 | archive-date = 2021-03-15 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210315093909/https://www.theverge.com/2012/5/7/3005044/roflcon-when-memes-go-mainstream | dead-url = no }}</ref>。萊尼·格林納不喜歡「我討厭沙堡」的迷因，因為她覺得這讓她那個實際上很喜歡沙堡的孩子成了一個會欺負人的孩子<ref name="the verge ROFLCon" />，不過她接受「成功小孩」的解釋。<ref name="abc news kidney transplant campaign" />

在迷因蔚為風潮後，萊尼將這張圖片授權給圖庫公司[[蓋帝圖像|蓋帝圖像]]<ref name="arizona state web culture conference">{{cite web | url = http://mashable.com/2012/05/10/child-memes/ | title = What to Expect When Your Kid Becomes a Meme | last = Erickson | first = Christine | work = [[Mashable|Mashable]] | date = 2012-05-10 | accessdate = 2015-04-16 | archive-date = 2021-01-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210109042402/https://mashable.com/2012/05/10/child-memes/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>，不過之後就改為自己持有<ref name="arizona state web culture conference" />，並在2012年對圖片申請版權保護，並在那之後將圖片授權給多家廣告商<ref name="verge jan2020"/>。這張圖片被用於飲料廣告和電信公司的廣告牌上<ref name="success kid advertisements">{{cite web | url = http://news.wjct.org/post/success-kid-jacksonville | title = 'Success Kid' Is From Jacksonville | last = Feagins | first = Karen | work = wjct NEWS | date = 2013-04-05 | accessdate = 2015-04-17 | archive-date = 2020-11-12 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201112013615/https://news.wjct.org/post/success-kid-jacksonville | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="virgin mobile licensing costs">{{cite web | url = http://www.searchenginejournal.com/use-memes-social-media-marketing-campaign/68701/ | title = How to Use Memes in Your Social Media Marketing Campaign | last = DeMers | first = Jason | work = Search Engine Journal | date = 2013-09-09 | accessdate = 2015-04-17 | archive-date = 2019-09-13 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190913212015/https://www.searchenginejournal.com/use-memes-social-media-marketing-campaign/68701/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>。2013年，她聘顧「迷因管理師」斑·拉許（Ben Lashes），作為她兒子的代理人<ref name="success kid advertisements" />，負責進行與這張照片有關的交易。包括把肖像印在{{link-en|熱門話題|Hot Topic}}推出的T恤上、張貼在{{link-en|睿俠|Radio Shack}}的辦公室內、出現在[[Xbox|Xbox]]的螢幕保護程式上<ref name="success kid advertisements" />，這張照片還被歐巴馬政府用來做為推行移民政策改革的宣傳圖<ref name="NY Daily News Success Kid White House">{{cite web | url = http://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/success-kid-meme-pass-immigration-reform-article-1.1376952 | title = White House tweets Success Kid meme urging Congress to pass immigration reform | last = Larson | first = Leslie | work = [[New_York_Daily_News|New York Daily News]] | date = 2013-06-19 | accessdate = 2015-04-16 | archive-date = 2020-10-21 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201021225207/https://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/success-kid-meme-pass-immigration-reform-article-1.1376952 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。這張宣傳對迷因的運用在推特上受到廣泛歡迎。<ref name="NY Daily News Success Kid White House"/>

萊尼也對未經授權就使用照片的人採取相應措施，一家煙火公司未經許可就在產品上貼上這張照片，因此遭到萊尼提告<ref name="fireworks company lawsuit">{{cite web | url = http://mashable.com/2015/02/25/success-kid-lawsuit/ | title = Boom! Success Kid's mom sues fireworks company for using his image | last = Wasserman | first = Todd | work = [[Mashable|Mashable]] | date = 2015-02-25 | accessdate = 2015-04-16 | archive-date = 2020-11-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201129055316/https://mashable.com/2015/02/25/success-kid-lawsuit/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>。2020年1月，美國政治人物[[史提夫·金|史提夫·金]]未經允許就使用成功小孩的照片來進行募款，萊尼發了一封信函要求他[[停止並終止|停止並終止]]這項行為。<ref name="verge jan2020">{{cite web | url = https://www.theverge.com/2020/1/28/21111805/iowa-republican-meme-lawsuit-success-kid-mom-steve-king | title = Iowa Republican receives cease-and-desist for using a beloved kid meme so the ‘Lefties stay triggered’ | first = Kim | last = Lyons | date = January 28, 2020 | accessdate = January 28, 2020 | work = [[The_Verge|The Verge]] | archive-date = 2021-03-08 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210308140338/https://www.theverge.com/2020/1/28/21111805/iowa-republican-meme-lawsuit-success-kid-mom-steve-king | dead-url = no }}</ref>

2012年，賈斯汀和萊尼在參與網路名人大會[[ROFLCon|ROFLCon]]時，談到撫養孩子與保護孩子所擁有的品牌時所面臨的挑戰<ref name="arizona state web culture conference" />。許多人批評他們是在消費自己的孩子，萊尼對此回應，指出自己無法控制迷因的傳播，但也不擔心反效果，因為「最重要的是有更多人因為這張圖片而感到快樂。」<ref name="arizona state web culture conference" />

== GoFundMe活動 ==
在薩米出生前不久，他的父親賈斯汀（Justin）被診斷出患有腎臟衰竭，每週有三天必須接受四小時的透析治療<ref name="abc news kidney transplant campaign" />。2015年四月，萊尼在GoFundMe上發起募資活動，希望能募到75000美金，用於支付丈夫的醫療費用和腎臟移植費用。她原本將募資的重點放在丈夫的醫療需求，且不希望這個活動與「成功小孩」迷因扯上關係，但後來她改變主意。在那之後的五天內，她成功募得了來自300人、將近9000美元的捐款<ref name="abc news kidney transplant campaign" />。在活動訊息被轉貼到[[Reddit|Reddit]]後的幾天內，募款總額超過了83000美元<ref name="Metro UK Reddit posting">{{cite web|url=http://metro.co.uk/2015/04/15/success-kid-fundraising-target-smashed-after-redditor-posts-metro-article-5151979/|title=‘Success Kid’ fundraising target smashed after Redditor posts Metro article|last=Readhead|first=Harry|date=2015-04-15|work=Metro|accessdate=2015-04-16|archive-date=2021-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210227083200/http://metro.co.uk/2015/04/15/success-kid-fundraising-target-smashed-after-redditor-posts-metro-article-5151979/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。這個故事被多家媒體報導，包括[[ABC新聞|ABC新聞]]、[[有線電視新聞網|CNN]]、[[BuzzFeed|BuzzFeed]]、[[時代雜誌|時代雜誌]]、[[哈芬登郵報|哈芬登郵報]]及其它多家媒體<ref name="abc news kidney transplant campaign" /><ref name="cnn success kid" /><ref name="buzzfeed success kid">{{cite web | url = https://www.buzzfeed.com/rachelzarrell/the-real-boy-from-the-success-kid-meme-is-trying-to-get-his#.cqg6G3gYkJ | title = The Boy From The "Success Kid" Meme Is Trying To Get His Dad A Kidney | last = Zarrell | first = Rachel | work = [[BuzzFeed|BuzzFeed]] | date = 2015-04-14 | accessdate = 2015-04-16 | archive-date = 2017-11-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20171105180801/https://www.buzzfeed.com/rachelzarrell/the-real-boy-from-the-success-kid-meme-is-trying-to-get-his#.cqg6G3gYkJ | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="time success kid">{{cite web | url = http://time.com/3823341/success-kid-fundraiser-father-kidney-meme/ | title = Boy of ‘Success Kid’ Meme Fundraises For Father’s Kidney Transplant | last = Sifferlin | first = Alexandra | work = [[時代雜誌|時代雜誌]] | date = 2015-04-15 | accessdate = 2015-04-16 | archive-date = 2021-02-01 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210201224934/https://time.com/3823341/success-kid-fundraiser-father-kidney-meme/ | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="the huffington post success kid">{{cite web | url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/04/14/success-kid-dad-kidney_n_7063936.html | title = Dad Of Viral 'Success Kid' Needs A Kidney Transplant | last = Bologna | first = Caroline | work = [[哈芬登郵報|哈芬登郵報]] | date = 2015-04-14 | accessdate = 2015-04-16 | archive-date = 2016-09-10 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160910201702/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/04/14/success-kid-dad-kidney_n_7063936.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。2015年八月，ABC新聞報導賈斯汀接受了移植手術，術後狀況良好，已出院並逐漸康復。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Health/dad-success-kid-undergoes-successful-kidney-transplant/story?id=33159971|title=Dad of 'Success Kid' Gets Successful Kidney Transplant|date=2015-08-19|publisher=ABC News|access-date=2016-09-02|archive-date=2020-11-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201124121503/https://abcnews.go.com/Health/dad-success-kid-undergoes-successful-kidney-transplant/story?id=33159971|dead-url=no}}</ref>
